Package undecided

Interface Summary
Item This interface class describes the effects that the item type classes should have, namely activateEffect on either the PlayerTank or the EnemyTank.
Obstacle This interface is implemented by all the non user controlled objects on the field: crate, fire ring, barrier, spike pit, and TNT box.
Projectile  
Terrain This interface class simple describes the effect that different terrain will have on the PlayerTank and EnemyTank speed.
 

Class Summary
BubbleShield This class implements items and is a shield that protects the tank from projectiles for a short period of time.
Crate This class is the crate object which has health, a rectangle that will be used to determine object collisions, and a location.
EnemyProjectile The EnemyProjectile class is the bullets that either the AI or opponent of a PvP match tank will fire.
EnemyTank This class is the enemy tank and will control its AI, health, movements, etc.
Explosion This class will control the explosions for when either the EnemyTank or the PlayerTank is destroyed.
FireRing This class is the fire ring obstacle.
Grass This simple class simulates the speed on which the tanks will move if on grass.
Ice This simple class simulates the speed on which the tanks will move if on ice.
IceBlock This class is an item that will appear on any map.
ImmovableBlock This class is the immovable object which has health (-1), a rectangle that will be used to determine object collisions, and a location.
ItemCreator The ItemCreator class will determine when and where items should be created and placed onto an active map.
Level1 This class is the "level1" map for the campaign mode of tanks.
Level2 This class is the "level2" map for the campaign mode of tanks.
Level3 This class is the "level3" map for the campaign mode of tanks.
Level4 This class is the "level4" map for the campaign mode of tanks.
Level5 This class is the "level5" map for the campaign mode of tanks.
Map The map class is the class that keeps track of all objects that are on the board.
PlayerProjectile  
PlayerTank This class is the tank object that is controlled by the player that can be moved by arrow keys and shoot independently via the mouse.
Point This class is a point (overriding Java's Point class) that will be used to determine the location of tanks and obstacles
Sand This simple class simulates the speed on which the tanks will move if on sand.
SpeedBoost This class is an item that will appear on any map.
SpikePit This class is the SpikePit object which essentially destroys the PlayerTank if it moves over it on the field.
TankView This class is the primary battle view in which the player controls a single tank that can move through the arrow keys and shoot through the mouse.
TNT This class is the TNT object which essentially when destroyed, will deal damage to a certain radius around it.
 

Enum Summary
Direction This is an enum class that contains the constants NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, and WEST.
